Create a new image from a Dockerfile. 

podman build -t my-custom-image:v1 . 

This command builds an image named "my-custom-image" with the tag "v1" using the Dockerfile in the current directory. 

Push an image to a registry:  Upload a local image to a container registry. 

podman push my-custom-image:v1 docker.io/myusername/my-custom-image:v1 


Create and manage pods:  Podman supports pod management similar to Kubernetes. 

# Create a pod

podman pod create --name my-pod

# Run a container in the pod

podman run -d --pod my-pod --name container1 nginx:latest


# List pods
podman pod list

# Inspect a pod
podman pod inspect my-pod

# Remove a pod and its containers
podman pod rm -f my-pod







Create a volume
podman volume create my-data

# List volumes
podman volume list

# Use a volume in a container
podman run -d --name my-db -v my-data:/var/lib/mysql mysql:latest

# Remove a volume
podman volume rm my-data




# Create a network
podman network create my-network

# List networks
podman network list

# Run a container on a specific network
podman run -d --name my-app --network my-network nginx:latest

# Remove a network
podman network rm my-network






podman system prune --volumes



podman generate kube my-nginx > my-nginx-deployment.yaml


podman play kube my-nginx-deployment.yaml

podman system prune






